    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "If I was going to write a token standard again, I would exclude `to != 0x0` checks in the code, and then make up for it with `Clients MUST produce a warning before attempting to send to the 0x0 address if the user intention is to transfer.`\r\n\r\nBut as long as we have the current standards that are widely supported and there are no glaring errors with them, we should prefer consistency over minor innovations.",
