    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I don't really see reasons to allow use of 0x0 like any other address (in transfers or elsewhere), and I do see some reasons to disallow it, namely that it can show up accidentally in a few places: read from an uninitialized variable or in the return value of `ecrecover`. They are not particularly strong reasons but I think the net result is that we should treat the zero address specially and disallow its use in most places.",
